cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.EDU 

This paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze a dataset of peer grades in a course on algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of peer grading in an educational setting, which could fall under cs.EDU (Education). The paper also involves the analysis of data structures, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of statistical methods could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
